# Storybook Source Of Truth

For UI implementation work, Storybook is the canonical source of truth.

## Workflow Contract

1. Figma -> Storybook
   - Use Figma to explore and translate design decisions into Storybook stories/components.
   - Do not treat Figma as the final implementation API.

2. Storybook -> App Code
   - Build app UI from existing Storybook components and documented variants/props.
   - If a Storybook component exists, it must be reused instead of recreated.

## Strict Rules

- No custom replacement for existing Storybook components (e.g., Button, fields, list items).
- No hardcoded visual values when tokens/classes/components already exist.
- Prefer existing typography utility classes over manual font-size/line-height.
- If mapping is unclear, stop and ask before coding.

## Required Pre-Code Output

- List Storybook story IDs/URLs used for implementation.
- List mapped app components that will reuse those Storybook components.

## Required Completion Audit

- Component reuse: confirmed
- Typography classes: confirmed
- Token usage (color/spacing/radius): confirmed
- Hardcoded visual overrides: none
